description: From Narragansett munnawhatteaug (“they fertilize”), influenced by poghaden.

entries.meaning: Any of several species of fish in the genera Brevoortia and Ethmidium, used for fish meal, fish oil, fertilizer, and bait.
examples: Synonyms: (US regional) bunker, mossbanker, mossbunker, (obsolete) mossyback, pauhagen, poghaden
